name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 4237 S Cheney Spokane Rd, Spokane WA, 99224
info:
FREE BREAKFAST!!!  Come and join Consistent Care Services and Chaps restaurant to get vaccinated for COVID-19 and participate in helping get the world get back on track. Chaps is giving anyone who gets vaccinated a free cup of Chaps signature oatmeal AND you’ll receive a $10 Gift Certificate to Chaps to use that day or come back another time and enjoy some of their amazing food and drinks! 
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase. (If 12-17 years old must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) 
***Vaccinations are by appointment only. This clinic is located at 4237 S. Cheney Spokane Rd., Spokane WA 99224***
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic AND bring your insurance card***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Arlington Airport Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
*************THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC********** 

Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
